The Cu2O/CuO(100) 6 × 3 supercell structure (the CuO surface was evolved from the Cu2O(100) surface) in Fig. 2a consists of 9 layers of Cu2O(100), 12 layers of CuO, and 4 transition layers in between14, with the structure being cleaved along the direction of the scissors as indicated. As Cu2O is a cubic lattice, we assume that the CuO lattice evolved from it shares the same cubic geometry, thus we set the cleavage angle to 35.26°(tan−12\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
